ocal of that for the equilibrium concentration. This behaviour\nleads to almost identical CV- and ZP-based values for the self-diffusion\ncoefficient. Obviously, this agreement is accidental. The consideration of the\ntemperature dependence of the magnetization yields self-diffusion data in very\ngood agreement with experiments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Apr 2015 13:26:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 10 Jun 2015 06:58:14 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 15 Jul 2015 06:11:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-11"}
